How to install esp8266 library in arduino IDE

How to install esp8266 library in arduino IDE
=============================================

### Step1: copy this link into your arduino IDE: http://arduino.esp8266.com/stable/package\_esp8266com\_index.json

Image:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Step2: Go to the board manger and type "esp8266" and install the package

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Step3: Test your library

#### Open the example ESP8266WiFi -> WiFiScan  
and upload the code(remember to setup your board)  
if you meet some trouble, Google is your good friend!  
You upload successful, open your serial moniter,there will show all WiFis your board discovered.
